SkullFACE FunFact: On this date in 2004 the first legal same-sex marriages in the U.S. are performed in the state of Massachusetts. Massuchusetts became the first staye in the US and just the sixth jurisdiction in the world to legalize same-sex marriage. The struggle to recieve civil marriage rights and benefits for same-sex couples began in the US during the 1970's and thanks to the Supreme Judicial Court's decision in Goodridge v. Department of Public Health six months earlier that dream became a reality.
